    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-20T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="468"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/8–351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Union of South Africa</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-20T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 20, 1951—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes procedures suggested para four
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 38 Aug 3, wld not be acceptable
                    necessary majority members <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> who wld regard
                    nomination of body, which presumably comparable Comite rather than Comm in <hi
                        rend="italic">Ad Hoc</hi> Comite draft, as irregular and impracticable.
                    Unlikely that non-administering members who constitute large majority <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> wld agree to complete exclusion from body.
                    Moreover, inclusion non-administering members probably advantageous since wld
                    obviate adverse criticism which wld certainly arise in <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> if reports approved <pb facs="0712" n="690" xml:id="pg_690"/> by
                    body composed entirely administering countries. Furthermore US position based on
                    respect for <gloss target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss> advisory opinion and <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> doubtful suggested procedure consistent with
                    this position. Therefore, substance para four shld not be put forward as US
                    suggestion nor shld <gloss target="#t_SA1">SA</gloss> be encouraged advance such
                    suggestion. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes no deviation from
                    Comite proposal shld be put forward at this time in order avoid possible
                    misunderstanding between Union and Comite.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
